{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566938","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566938"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:51:18+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:51:18+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18910"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18910","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18910"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.86,0.01,0.11,0.01,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11643"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80161"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11643","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11643"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18910"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65438"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"17"},{"type":"tags","id":"18"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"2425"},{"type":"tags","id":"2628"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5675"},{"type":"tags","id":"5759"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11322"},{"type":"tags","id":"11323"},{"type":"tags","id":"11354"},{"type":"tags","id":"11373"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27388"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27391"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80161","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80161"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA General Practitioner has personal religious beliefs that conflict with providing certain medical procedures that are legal and commonly requested by patients.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the appropriate professional response to managing this conflict between personal beliefs and professional obligations?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Inform patients of the objection and refer to other providers","Refuse to see any patients who might request these procedures","Provide all procedures despite personal objections","Withhold information about available procedures","Decline all procedures regardless of urgency"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct approach is to \u003Cstrong\u003Einform patients of the objection and refer to other providers\u003C/strong\u003E. This balances respect for the practitioner\u0027s personal beliefs with the professional obligation to ensure patients can access legal healthcare services.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect approaches are problematic because:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERefuse to see any patients who might request these procedures\u003C/strong\u003E - This discriminates against patients and fails to fulfill professional obligations to provide care\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProvide all procedures despite personal objections\u003C/strong\u003E - While this ensures patient care, it unnecessarily compromises the practitioner\u0027s genuine moral beliefs when alternatives exist\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWithhold information about available procedures\u003C/strong\u003E - This violates the principle of informed consent and the duty to provide accurate health information\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecline all procedures regardless of urgency\u003C/strong\u003E - This fails to recognise that the duty of care must take precedence in emergencies\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHealthcare professionals must balance their right to conscientious objection with professional obligations. This includes:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EInforming patients of their objection early in the consultation\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EProviding information about alternative care options\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EEnsuring timely referral to willing practitioners\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003ESetting aside personal beliefs in emergencies where delay would risk patient harm\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Healthcare professionals have a right to conscientious objection but must ensure patient care is not compromised.","When exercising conscientious objection, practitioners must inform patients of their objection and provide information about alternative care options.","The duty of care to patients takes precedence over personal beliefs in emergency situations."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx.","Savulescu J. Conscientious objection in medicine. BMJ. 2006 Feb 4;332(7536):294-7. Available at: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC1360408/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65438"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18910"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65438","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65438"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-17T20:48:29+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-17T20:49:33+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11643"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80161"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"17","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/17"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude07","name":"Bioethics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"